webpackJsonp([0xbae3da36c857],{577:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{post:{id:"/Users/varya/WebDev/Personal/varya.github.com/content/posts/patterned-triangle/index_en.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>As you might know, I recently run the <a href="https://github.com/toivonen/bem-love">BEM\nLOVE</a> project to demonstrate how blocks\ncan communicate with JavaScript.<excerpt/></p>\n<p>The first example is dull enough; <a href="http://toivonen.github.com/bem-love/desktop.bundles/ask-her-what-music-she-likes/ask-her-what-music-she-likes.html">a boy, a girl and the heartless\nworld</a>.</p>\n<p>Today, I was going to start with another one with a boy plunging into\ndifficulties of choice. He has <a href="http://toivonen.github.com/bem-love/desktop.bundles/choose-the-one/choose-the-one.html">two girls to\nask</a>.\nSuddenly there is a <strong>challenge for you</strong>.</p>\n<p>Let’s think if it’s possible to attract a boy with a booooooring one-colour\ndress? Seems like no.<br/>\nSo, the girls in the page are in need of nice patterned dresses. Any ideas on\nhow to code a patterned triangle in CSS?</p>\n<h3>Where to code?</h3>\n<p>To dress the girls excellenty and toppingly you need just three steps:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fork the project and <a href="https://github.com/toivonen/bem-love#how-to-contribute">run the\nserver</a>.</li>\n<li><a href="https://github.com/toivonen/bem-love/tree/master/desktop.bundles/choose-the-one/blocks/girl/_dressed">Contribute to modifiers</a></li>\n<li>Make your pull request</li>\n</ul>',fields:{slug:"en/issues/patterned-triangle/",prefix:"",disqusIdentifier:"en-issues-patterned-triangle"},frontmatter:{title:"Patterned triangles with  CSS",date:"19 March 2013",v2:null,old:!0,tumblr:null,meta:null,cover:null}},authornote:{id:"/Users/varya/WebDev/Personal/varya.github.com/content/parts/author.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p><strong>Mr. Gatsby</strong> Proin ornare ligula eu tellus tempus elementum. Aenean <a href="/">bibendum</a> iaculis mi, nec blandit lacus interdum vitae. Vestibulum non nibh risus, a scelerisque purus. Blandit lacus interdum vitae. Vestibulum non nibh risus, a scelerisque purus.</p>'},site:{siteMetadata:{siteUrl:"http://varya.me/"}}},pathContext:{slug:"en/issues/patterned-triangle/",prev:{id:"/Users/varya/WebDev/Personal/varya.github.com/content/posts/on-the-unicorn-law/index_en.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",fields:{slug:"en/posts/on-the-unicorn-law/",prefix:"",lang:"en",disqusIdentifier:"posts-on-the-unicorn-law-index-en"},frontmatter:{title:"An answer to the question which should not have been asked"}},next:{id:"/Users/varya/WebDev/Personal/varya.github.com/content/posts/learn-english/index_ru.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",fields:{slug:"ru/issues/learn-english/",prefix:"",lang:"ru",disqusIdentifier:"ru-issues-learn-english"},frontmatter:{title:"Мой опыт изучения английского"}}}}}});
